{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c99d4284-706f-4c07-9c09-e768cfe90e04","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23050ff8-3439-435d-8367-5c74f9c449ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"A029:14C0A3:17DCEDC:1B1B706:69FE8A1E"},"id":"ba33e2ad-650a-434e-862b-bbf8b62472c4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:13:08.714Z","parentId":"c0e56eae-2489-4ead-8920-06ab1265e855"}
